Japanese: ガロイ親方＿戦闘中真剣

English: Good news.

Japanese:
旧式のマリオネーションギアが
タダで手に入るかもしれん。
English: We might be able to get our hands on an old-fashioned Marionation Gear for free.

Japanese: メリッサ＿ちょっとした驚き

English: Really?

Japanese: タダってのはすげぇな。
English: Anything's worth it for free.

Japanese: ガロイ親方＿戦闘中真剣

ランバートの店に
古いやつがあるらしい。
それを譲ってくれるとさ。
English: Seems that Lambert's got an obsolete model in his shop. That's what he's proposing to let us have.

Japanese:
/pの武勇伝が
伝わったらしくてな。
English: Looks like he heard about /p's brave battle.

Japanese:
何かの役にたてば、
ということらしい。
English: He thinks it might come in handy for something.

We're heading out soon.
Get a move on, /p!

Japanese:
ランバートの店は、
マリオネーションギア用の
パーツ工房だよ。
English: Lambert's store is a studio where you can get parts for Marionation Gear.

Japanese:
人形を強化するためのパーツを
売っているところさ。
English: He sells parts that can be used to strengthen mechs.
It's not far from here.
Yo, Galouye.

Japanese:
聞いたぜ。
オートマンを倒したらしいな。
English:
I heard the news.
So, you took down an Automan.

Japanese: ガロイ親方＿戦闘中真剣

English: Yeah.

Japanese:
それでマリオネーションギアを
提供してくれるってのは
本当なのか？
English: Since we're on the topic, is it true that you've got a Marionation Gear for us?
It is.

Japanese:
作業用の旧式だが
何かの役にはたつだろう。
English: It's a bit old for manual labour, but it should still be useful for something.

Japanese:
整備はしてある。
持ってけよ。
English:
I've finished with the repair work.
It's all yours.
So, who's going to be piloting it?
This one.

Japanese: ランバート＿ちょっとした驚き

English: What the-!?
But he's just a lad, ain't he?

Japanese: ガロイ親方＿戦闘中真剣
子供だが、なかなかの腕だ。
English: He may be young, but he's exceptionally skilled.

Japanese:
待ってくれよ。
いくらなんでも、
そりゃねぇだろ。
English:
Hold on a minute.
No matter how skilled he might be, that's...

Japanese: なんならテストしてみるか？
English: Then, why don't you put him to the test?

Japanese:
よし。
ワシがこいつに乗る。
English:
All right.
I'll pilot this one.

Japanese:
タダでこいつをくれてやるのは、
何かの役にたつと思うからだ。
English: I was going to give this one away for free, but it looks like I'll be putting it to use first.

Japanese:
お遊びに使うつもりなら、
ごめんこうむる。
English: If you think I'm going to let you off lightly, you'll be sorely disappointed.

Japanese: ランバート＿機嫌が悪い
悪いがテストさせてもらうぞ。
English: Let's get this over with.

Japanese:
もし、一流の人形使いなら、
ワシなんぞ簡単に倒せるはず。
English: If you really are such a high class puppeteer, you ought to be able to easily defeat me.

Japanese:
ワシを倒したら、
この人形をやる。
English: In which case, I'll let you keep this mech.

Japanese:
/p、遠慮はいらねぇ。
やっちまいな。
English:
/p, there's no need to hold back.
Give him all you've got.
I've been working with mechs for over 40 years.

Japanese:
悪いが、お前さんよりは、
マリオネーションギアの使い方
を心得てるつもりだぞ。
English: I might be wrong, but I'm pretty sure I know a lot more about using Marionation Gear than you.
Here I come!
